.TH hsh 1 "Simple Shell Manual" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
reads commands from standard input and executes them.

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B hsh
program is a minimal implementation of a UNIX shell.  
It executes commands by searching for the corresponding program in the
directories stored in the PATH environment variable.  
It supports interactive and non-interactive modes.

This project is part of the SE curriculum and aims to introduce students to:
process creation, system calls, environment handling, tokenizing input, and
implementing basic built-in commands.

.SH FEATURES
- Command execution using fork and execve  
- PATH handling  
- Built-in commands: exit, env  
- Error messages similar to /bin/sh  

.SH AUTHORS
